<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870731-0055 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Pantera's Corp.</HL><DD> 07/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PANT PZATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Pantera's Corp., St. Louis, completed the acquisition of Pizza Inn Inc. of Dallas. Under terms, Pizza Inn holders may choose, for each share held, $3 cash and 0.828456 Pantera common share; or $4 cash plus a unit consisting of one Pantera's share and one right. The right entitles a Pizza Inn holder who holds Pantera's stock for one year after the merger to receive as much as an additional 0.55 share if Pantera's share price averages less than $7 during the 90 days ending on the first anniversary of the merger. To finance the purchase, the pizza restaurant operator has entered an agreement with Lloyds Bank PLC and Kleinwort Benson Ltd., providing for a $35 million credit facility. </TEXT></DOC>